@node "1" ""
IBB V2.0 (Internet Bank Book) is a utility which keeps a record of your calls
to internet including Time and Date of your call, the cost and rate at which
you were charged at depending on when you called.

These rates are calculated as follows (For NB, Canada)

Prime time (8am-6pm) (10 cents/min) 10 cents/60 sec=0.001666666666 cents/sec.

20% Discount(6pm-11pm)(8 cents/min) 8 cents/60 sec=0.00133333333333 cents/sec.

50% (5 cents/min) 5 cents/60 sec = 0.000833333333 cents/sec.

IBB updates the online charging each second up t to 16 decimal places.








@endnode

@node "Document_1" ""

                               Features
                               ~~~~~~~~


                             -- Buttons --


START - Starts the IBB program. While in operation it is not possible to
change the Charged Rate or RESET/SAVE.

STOP - Halts the IBB program. Pressing START after a stop will resume IBB.
Save/Rate Menus Enabled.

RESET - Resets amount charged to 0$ RATE menu  and SAVE enabled.

SAVE - Will Save current log in your IBB:log directory called Balance.log.

CONFIG  - Allows to change Rate changed per hour. Rate charged must
          be entered as follows, ex:  0.05 (5 cents/min)
                                             0.10 (10 cents/min)
                                             0.99 (99 cents/min max)

        - Rates above 0.99 cents/min will prevent CFG save.

        - Cannot be acessed while IBB is 'STARTed'.

        - Variables for the charge rate field are stored in
          IBB:var  as rate1.var rate2.var and rate3.var


View    - conveniantly View Log file with internal reader. (Bonus)


Delete  - Delete Log file from IBB:log directory. (V3.0 only)
          Abort will abort deletion,and Delete will Delete the log file.
          (Can get anymore redundant that that..)
          All options/windows except for WB are not accesible when a
          Delete Requester is present.
          



                             -- Menus --


DISCOUNT Changes the rate at which you are changed. This option is set to
RATE 3  at startup by default. Rate chosen will be ghosted.


Tech info: The program divides the rate,ex: 0.05/60 sec. to calculate the
amount charged per second. These fields do not accept any amount above 1$ per
minute,or a maximum of 0.99 dollars per minute (99 cents).



@endnode

